<paragraph blockId="11.[187,1399,1892,2025]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,264,1892,1919]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">Fig. 7.</emphasis>
Habitat and host plant of 
<taxonomicName authority="Vargas, 2021" authorityName="Vargas" authorityYear="2021" box="[553,810,1893,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Heliodinidae" genus="Helioandesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarregai" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[553,810,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">Helioandesia tarregai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[817,987,1893,1919]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[989,1010,1892,1918]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">A</emphasis>
. The type locality near Zapahuira Village at about 3400 m elevation on the western slopes of the Andes of the Parinacota Province, northern Chile. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[270,290,1963,1989]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">B</emphasis>
. The host plant 
<taxonomicName authority="(Reiche) Heimerl" authorityName="Heimerl" authorityYear="1932" baseAuthorityName="Reiche" box="[491,889,1963,1990]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nyctaginaceae" genus="Mirabilis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acuta">
<emphasis box="[491,674,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">Mirabilis acuta</emphasis>
(Reiche) Heimerl
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[907,1087,1963,1990]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nyctaginaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Nyctaginaceae</taxonomicName>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1110,1129,1963,1989]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">C</emphasis>
. Detail of the damage pattern on a leaf of the host. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[525,546,1998,2024]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">D</emphasis>
. Flower of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heimerl" authorityYear="1932" baseAuthorityName="Reiche" box="[683,787,1999,2024]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nyctaginaceae" genus="Mirabilis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acuta">
<emphasis box="[683,787,1999,2024]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">M. acuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
